text.section:
If any forest or park warden sees a forest fire, or is requested by a fire company to assist with a fire plow or provide incident command expertise at the scene, the forest or park warden shall:
Go immediately to the fire and employ those persons and means as the forest or park warden deems necessary to extinguish the fire;
Keep an itemized account of all expenses thus incurred and send the account immediately to the Secretary;
Control and direct any person and apparatus engaged in extinguishing forest fires;
Summon inhabitants of the county over the age of 18 years, if able, to assist in extinguishing fires, and also require use of personal property needed for this purpose; and
Use the members of the Junior Forest Fire Fighters Service between the ages of 14 and 18 years inclusive, either paid or unpaid, provided they have the written consent of their parents or guardians.
